  • Classes in undirectedgraph used by MinSpantree 
    Class and Description
    UGNode
    A class representing the Vertices of an Undirected Graph, here called a Node, or UGNode denoting that it is a part of an |U|ndirected |G|raph The class has a generic value-type that must extend UGNodeInterface in order to ensure that the value has a method for calculating its relative weight to another Vertex(UGNode)
    UGNodeInterface
    An interface that must be implemented by a value saved in a Vertex to ensure that it can calculate a relative edge to another vertex's value
